-Hello.
-Hi.

106
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:03,000
You're a new face.

107
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:05,240
-Have you worked in this field?
-Yes.

108
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:07,160
I guess I have.

109
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:09,760
I see. Which shows have you made?

110
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:13,960
Didn't you do variety shows?
Then what did you do?

111
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,960
Are you the director of Variety Team?

112
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,480
Don't you know who I am?

113
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:24,440
I see. Did you get in through connections?

114
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:28,640
I'm Park Woong-soo.

115
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,280
You know "One Must Eat To Live",
don't you?

116
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,640
I'm the one who made it.

117
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:34,640
It's not easy being a director
of a variety show.

118
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:37,320
Sure, it might look cool and easy.

119
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:39,159
It must look like a job
where you can slack off.

120
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,400
What? "Slack off"?

121
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,960
What are you talking about?
This is like a battlefield.

122
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:44,880
-Of course it...
-Variety Team is tough.

123
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,360
You should think it through.

124
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:48,520
Do you know how much work
is required to get the funds

125
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,960
for an international shoot?

126
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:52,160
Of course, companies sponsor
on shows that I do,

127
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,560
but everyone else is hardly holding on.

128
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,720
The director has to bring in
the funds themselves?

129
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:58,720
You're so naive.

130
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,560
Who else would do it
other than the director?

131
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:02,120
Shooting the show is trivial work.

132
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:04,200
Securing sponsors is the real part
of the job.

133
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,600
Just take it easy with your job.

134
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:11,840
It's not like you're trying to get
scouted to a cable channel, are you?

135
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,160
Especially if you landed the job
through connections.

136
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:18,360
By the way, you're really handsome
for a director.

137
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,840
Let me take a look.

138
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,960
Is this necessary for a director?

139
