but you're way too handsome.

140
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:26,480
Gosh, what a work of art.

141
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,680
What do you think you're doing?

142
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:29,120
Good morning, Chief.

143
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,040
Sir...

144
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:41,480
Haven't you taught your employees?

145
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:42,760
What did I do wrong this time?

146
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:46,120
This guy here. He has a rotten mentality.

147
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,320
You jerk.

148
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:53,520
You need to teach them
the right attitude first.

149
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,080
He told me to take it easy.

150
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:57,080
Why are all the employees just like you?

151
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,440
I'm sorry.

152
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:00,720
Hey.

153
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,200
When did you start working here?

154
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:04,480
You punk.

155
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:05,760
You better work properly.

156
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,400
You should be worth your paycheck.

157
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:11,080
You said we have a program planning
meeting, right? Where is it at?

158
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,680
Are all of you out of your minds?

159
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,640
Don't you know what year it is?

160
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:19,560
Do you think such proposals will work?

161
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:22,840
This is why people say
you're not worth your paycheck.

162
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:28,120
Do you think we're still in the 1990s?

163
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:31,560
Even broadcasting stations could go under.

164
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,640
We can only survive if we do our best.

165
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:36,800
Why do you think this happened
to broadcasting stations, Mr. Son?

166
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:41,160
What? Why? Well...

167
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,400
It's because...

168
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:44,280
I think this happened

169
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:47,800
because the one at the top hasn't changed.

170
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:49,560
My opinion is that the higher-ups

171
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,800
who only talk are the problems.

172
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:53,800
You annihilate talents who are creative,

173
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:56,560
and you break their challenging
and experimental spirits.

174
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,440
What are you talking about?

175
00:10:58,520 --> 00:10:59,760
You only focus on the ratings,

176
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:01,640
so you only end up making shows
that are safe.

177
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:05,040
That's how we end up
with the same shows everywhere.

178
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,840
Are there any shows in Korea

179
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:08,640
that the viewers actually want to see?

180
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,360
They don't have a choice.

181
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,480
They have to watch whatever we're airing.

182
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:14,280
There are cable channels
and online platforms too.

183
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,800
It's fierce out there,
yet you expect to survive

184
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:18,560
while thinking so backwardly?

185
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:22,120
I watched television like crazy
for the last few days

186
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,440
since I had to learn
the broadcasting trend.

187
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:27,200
So, Ma Dong...

188
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:30,960
Anyway, do you have an idea?

189
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:34,080
I came up with a few items.

190
