For example, we can set up
an observational camera.

191
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,400
It's an amalgamation
of documentary and variety shows.

192
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:40,680
In the end, variety shows

193
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,840
are meant to show humans.

194
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,920
We'll find an island,

195
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,440
and a few celebrities will go there

196
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:50,480
to make 3 meals a day. 3 meals a day.

197
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:54,840
Should I continue?

198
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:00,280
How about this?

199
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:03,120
We'll make singers wear masks
so no one knows who they are,

200
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,880
then we'll make them compete against
each other.

201
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:05,840
-"King of Mask Singer".
-Survival games

202
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:08,120
always work, you know.

203
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,600
They can be ranked.

204
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:18,280
What's with everyone?

205
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,040
You seem unenthusiastic.

206
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:25,000
What is this?

207
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:29,000
Do people drink soda without sugar now?

208
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,560
Are you trying to be funny?

209
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:43,640
What is this supposed to taste like?

210
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,840
Freud

211
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:49,800
used the desire to eat,
have sex, and excrete

212
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:51,840
as the basis

213
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:55,040
to analyze dreams.

214
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:58,240
Through our dreams,

215
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:00,480
our secret subconscious

216
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:04,240
(In 20 years, Hwang Byung-sim
would look just like him.)

217
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:06,680
Being conscious about our subconscious

218
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,040
is Freud's

219
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,840
-basic theory.
(-Gosh, this is boring.)

220
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,400
(After sleeping for 20 years,
how can I be sleepy again?)

221
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:17,800
Our goal is to understand
what psychology is about.

222
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:22,120
That's all for today.

223
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:25,960
-Let's go.
-Thank you.

224
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,560
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

225
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,680
-Wait!
-Professor.

226
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:35,160
We haven't received the syllabus yet.

227
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,560
What?

228
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:44,720
This is cool.

229
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,480
So I should use this.

230
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:53,080
Dong-chan, we should probably
hide your identity.

231
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:55,840
Even if I treat you casually
when others are around,

232
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:57,400
-please understand
-Sure.

233
00:13:57,560 --> 00:14:00,320
But when we're alone, I won't be
polite to you. Is that okay?

234
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:03,120
Why would you even ask?
You've never been polite to me.

235
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:07,360
Hyun-gi, you've grown a lot, by the way.

236
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:11,520
I'll be 50 soon.
I'm not sure that's appropriate.

237
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,920
Right. You sure have aged.

238
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:19,160
I do feel a bit uncomfortable
talking so casually to you.

239
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:21,240
No way. You look absolutely comfortable.

240
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:23,360
I never cared about hierarchy
in the old days either.

241
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,360
I remember that.

242
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:26,920
That's why I can treat you casually
so easily now.

243
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:30,200
Regardless of age, I can't stand
anyone talking nonsense.

244
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:34,320
Of course. You didn't fear anything
then, and neither do you now.

245
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:35,760
You're right.

246
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:36,880
Dong-chan.

247
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:41,320
I'm saying this to help you,
so please don't take it personally.

248
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:42,840
What is it? Go ahead.

249
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:45,320
I've been thinking about it,

250
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:48,080
and I'm afraid your creativity
got frozen that day

251
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:50,520
along with your brain.

252
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,560
Your creativity is completely gone.

253
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:55,320
What? My creativity is gone?

254
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,640
Are you done?

255
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,600
You said I could say it.

256
00:14:58,680 --> 00:15:00,560
Yes! Say anything you want.
I'm not stopping you.

257
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:03,080
Gosh, this is frustrating.

258
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:06,320
It took me a lot of courage
to tell you this.

259
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:10,120
The world is changing fast.
We have to work hard

260
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:12,640
to find out what our viewers want
to become successful.

261
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:16,160
That's what you told me 20 years ago
when I was an assistant director.

262
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:18,640
And that's exactly
what I want to tell you right now.

263
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:21,640
Otherwise, you won't survive
in Variety Team.

264
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:25,640
All right. I'll work harder.

265
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:27,440
A variety show director has to be

266
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:30,960
sensitive to change. You know that
better than anyone else.

267
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:33,240
Keeping up with the times is
not enough. You have to be ahead.

268
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:36,320
I get it! But I need some time.

269
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:38,000
I'm Ma Dong-chan.
I can do anything I set my mind to.

270
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:46,960
-Hello.
(-This is Ko Mi-ran.)

271
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,440
Ms. Ko?

272
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:53,200
How did you get my...

273
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:56,240
My phone didn't work,
so I gave her your number.

274
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:58,960
Why are you stuttering?
Did you do anything wrong?

275
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:00,040
No.

276
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:04,320
-Hello.
-Based on my memorandum,

277
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:06,160
I want a meeting
with the broadcasting station.

278
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:08,720
Let's meet in a week.

279
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:14,120
-Are you still there?
-Yes, I am.

280
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:16,000
Let's talk more in person.

281
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,640
The two of us?

282
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:21,760
No. I want to meet everyone
involved in this at the station.

283
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,840
President Kim!

284
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:28,400
What is it now?

285
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:31,120
Ko Mi-ran wants to meet us.

286
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:32,640
-What?
-And she said

287
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:35,360
something about her memorandum.

288
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:38,360
-I have no idea what that is.
-Her memorandum?

289
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:41,720
Her memorandum

290
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:45,320
Mr. President, I had to go through hoops

291
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:48,920
to persuade Dong-chan
to participate in this experiment.

292
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:51,760
He'll have to risk his life
for the project.

293
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:54,160
It's not an easy decision to make
for a regular director.

294
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:57,120
But I reviewed the experiment
from many different angles,

295
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:59,880
and it looked absolutely solid.
That's how I persuaded him.

296
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:02,840
President, if we make this work,

297
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:05,119
it'll be a huge plus for not only
the reputation of our station

298
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:09,040
but also for your political career.

299
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:11,720
Yes.

300
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:17,440
(Chief Director Kim Hong-suk)

301
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:19,520
Sir, I'll come to see you later.

302
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:20,760
Okay.

303
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:24,920
Ms. Ko, welcome.

304
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:27,359
Have a seat.

305
00:17:28,079 --> 00:17:30,680
You don't have to worry about that.

306
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:32,640
I'll persuade Director Ma.

307
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:35,880
Now that you said yes,
he must be getting cold feet.

308
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:37,240
You're doing it, right?

309
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:38,960
Yes, I am.

310
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:40,240
Of course.

311
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:43,920
This will help you land a job later
more than any experience.

312
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:48,920
The first cryonics experiment
subject like the first astronaut.

313
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,200
That sounds all good.

314
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:58,400
But why don't we sign a memorandum first?

315
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,400
A memorandum?

316
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,440
Professor Hwang, do you recognize me?

317
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:37,840
I'm Gi-bum. Jo Gi-bum, your assistant.

318
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,560
My assistant?

319
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:41,840
Yes. You did it.

320
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:43,560
Your cryonics experiment succeeded.

321
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:46,760
It didn't only last for 24 hours.
It lasted for 20 years.

322
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:49,120
My cryonics experiment?

323
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:52,240
Do you remember anything?

324
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:55,360
-Cryonics.
-Cry...

325
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,760
I want to cry.

326
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:04,480
Okay.

327
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:12,600
I'll make sure your memories come back.

328
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,440
That will solve everything.

329
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,800
You can't eat it. It's not candy.

330
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,480
Professor Hwang, calm down.

331
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:30,240
Look at me.

332
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:33,520
-Hang in there.
-Look at my finger.

333
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:36,280
Clench your fist.

334
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:39,360
Slowly. Clench it tight.

335
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:41,240
Clench your fist.

336
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:48,280
Professor Hwang. My goodness.

337
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:07,480
Is this what you use for editing now?

338
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:09,240
I can't believe it.

339
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,240
Aren't you cold?

340
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:14,360
If you're cold, put on more clothes.
I can't take off any more clothes.

341
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:19,440
This was Korea's biggest event in 2002.

342
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,720
Korea made it to the World Cup semifinals.

343
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:24,640
I edited it myself just for you.

344
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:27,240
A Summary of 20 Years of World History.

345
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:29,720
I'm sure you left out
the most important events.

346
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,400
"Director Ma Dong-chan's
cryonics experiment".

347
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,080
"Ma Dong-chan went missing."

348
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:38,480
Unbelievable. A black man
became the US president?

349
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:41,400
We even had a female president.

350
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:44,200
She's behind bars now though.

351
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:48,640
So the current Korean president is
Moon Jae-in. Who's the US president?

352
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:51,640
Donald Trump. He used to run
a real estate business.

353
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,640
Times sure have changed, I guess.

354
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:57,120
Who's this woman, by the way?

355
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:00,760
Oh, she? She's the woman
I had an affair with.

356
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:03,840
And why are you showing her to me?

357
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,920
What contribution has she made
to the world history?

358
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,840
I just thought you should know.

359
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:11,320
-Why?
-I'm a variety show director.

360
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:14,280
I want every video I make
to be extraordinary.

361
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,440
Gosh.

362
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:19,560
Isn't she beautiful?

363
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:21,920
What should I do not to end up like you?

364
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,280
Get a cell phone first.

365
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:31,120
That's called Tetris Dance.

366
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:32,600
I met her while making a show about it.

367
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:34,640
Don't say another word.

368
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:35,720
Fine.

369
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:39,280
Are you cold?

370
00:21:40,560 --> 00:21:41,840
Do you mean he was hired

371
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:43,200
through his connections
with News Department Chief?

372
00:21:43,280 --> 00:21:45,360
I'm sure. Didn't you all see that?

373
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:47,520
He brought up "King of Mask Singer"
and "Three Meals a Day".

374
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:49,120
He's not qualified at all.

375
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,760
Chief couldn't say anything to him either.

376
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:53,200
He seemed to be so intimidated.

377
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:56,120
Is News Department Chief so powerful?

378
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:57,800
Here's something I heard.

379
00:21:57,880 --> 00:22:00,080
You've all heard about a variety
show director who mysteriously disappeared

380
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:02,000
in the middle of
shooting a show 20 years ago, right?

381
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:03,040
-Of course.
-Of course.

382
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:04,400
Everyone's heard about it.

383
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:06,160
It's a legend that's been
passed down in Variety Team.

384
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:08,400
Some people say the new hire is that guy.

385
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:09,480
No way.

386
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,080
If he joined the station 20 years ago,

387
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:12,680
he must have been at least 26 years old.

388
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:14,520
That means he's at least 46 years old now.

389
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,120
You didn't see his face?

390
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:19,000
-He can't be older than 30.
-He's right. That's absurd.

391
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,400
You don't know that.

392
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:23,320
When he went missing,
it was all over the news.

393
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,240
But after a while, a gag order was issued.

394
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:26,560
All the footage was deleted too.

395
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:28,720
But apparently,
many people had already seen it,

396
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,240
and some information started circulating.

397
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:33,720
And the new hire is
the director who went missing.

398
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:37,720
If anyone hears you say that,
you'll be fired.

399
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:39,320
Be careful, everyone.

400
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:42,960
Moreover, he used to be
a legendary variety show director.

401
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:44,280
A genius planner.

402
00:22:44,360 --> 00:22:46,240
That's how a legend should end.

403
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:54,120
He's seriously good-looking.

404
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:56,680
I'd love to work with him
as an assistant director.

405
00:22:56,760 --> 00:22:58,200
That also proves that he has connections.

406
00:22:58,360 --> 00:22:59,640
A director can never look that good.

407
00:22:59,720 --> 00:23:01,680
Right. All directors look like you.

408
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:07,560
By the way, what is Ko Mi-ran
planning to do to us?

409
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:08,800
I don't know.

410
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:12,240
I have a bad feeling about this.
It's making me nervous.

411
00:23:39,040 --> 00:23:40,080
What?

412
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:47,280
(Leslie Cheung died on April Fools' Day.)

413
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:48,880
(It felt like a lie.)

414
00:24:05,040 --> 00:24:07,200
I can't remember anything!

415
00:24:18,840 --> 00:24:20,640
(1,000 won)

416
00:24:22,320 --> 00:24:23,440
50,000 won?

417
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:28,160
-Hello, everyone!
-Hello, everyone!

418
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:29,520
You're watching "Run, Quick Man".

419
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:30,960
-Look over there.
-My gosh.

420
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:33,520
Hey, what in the world is that?

421
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,520
It's called a drone.

422
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:37,000
"Drone"? How high does it fly?

423
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:52,560
Are you hot, my baby?

424
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:06,200
Dogs are everywhere.

425
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:08,080
Frozen squid.

426
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:10,680
Thawed squid.

427
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:12,920
Frozen dumplings. Thawed dumplings.

428
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:14,280
"Thaw".

429
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:17,240
Frozen...

430
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:18,440
They're thawed...

431
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:30,560
Professor Hwang, do you remember anything?

432
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:47,920
Professor Hwang.

433
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:51,600
You need to remember
who were inside those capsules.

434
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:53,280
Those two people woke up.

435
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:57,040
But they'll be in danger
if you don't retrieve your memory.

436
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:23,960
Oh, gosh.

437
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:28,680
Hello.

438
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:56,440
(Memorandum)

439
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:06,600
Hello.

440
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:10,520
I'm Ko Mi-ran,
and I turned 44 years old this year.

441
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:14,160
I'm 48.

442
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:21,320
Why don't you all take a look
at the memorandum?

443
00:27:26,360 --> 00:27:27,640
Did everyone read it?

444
00:27:28,280 --> 00:27:30,120
Yes, well...

445
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:32,840
I fully understand the situation you're in

446
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:34,720
and what you're trying to say.

447
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:37,080
The broadcasting station

448
00:27:37,240 --> 00:27:40,480
is very sorry about what happened to you,

449
00:27:40,560 --> 00:27:42,600
and we'd like to sincerely apologize...

450
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:47,040
Listen to me. I'm not here
to get an apology.

451
00:27:47,120 --> 00:27:48,320
I don't need an apology.

452
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,880
Do you really think you can end this
with an apology?

453
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:51,280
No, of course not.

454
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:56,280
I ask for compensation.

455
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,400
Back in 1999,

456
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:07,600
I got 6.5 million won for agreeing
to be frozen for 24 hours.

457
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,040
Am I right, Director Ma?

458
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:10,520
Wasn't it five million won?

459
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:12,320
I paid her 1.5 million won
with my own money.

460
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:13,680
Oh, I see.

461
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:17,160
Then let's say you paid me
5 million won for 24 hours.

462
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:22,400
That's 200,000 won per hour.

463
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:26,320
There are 8,760 hours in 1 year.

464
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:32,160
So that's around 1.7 billion won per year.

465
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:34,440
And if I times that by 20...

466
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:38,040
Maybe the battery's out.

467
00:28:38,120 --> 00:28:39,240
What's going on?

468
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:40,960
Give me that.

469
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:58,240
Three...

470
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:01,560
3.54 billion won?

471
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,480
Did you hear that? That's my compensation.

472
00:29:03,840 --> 00:29:06,760
But of course,
that's excluding the difference

473
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:09,680
of the market price
compared to 20 years ago.

474
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:11,160
Let me get to my point.

475
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:15,840
20 years ago, the bus fare was 500 won.

476
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:18,040
But now, it's double that price.

477
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:23,320
You can round it down.

478
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,720
If we round it down...

479
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:29,640
70 billion won?

480
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:31,400
70 billion won.

481
00:29:31,640 --> 00:29:34,560
You owe me 70 billion won.

482
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:36,640
Hear me out, Ms. Ko.

483
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:40,480
We fully understand how upset
and frustrated you must feel.

484
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:43,280
But 70 billion won is
a huge amount of money.

485
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:45,640
Our broadcasting station

486
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,760
isn't even worth that much.

487
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:49,440
Is the broadcasting station broke?

488
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:51,480
Why are you talking
as if we're running a pop-up store?

489
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:52,840
That's going to make her anxious.

490
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:54,360
Be quiet!

491
00:29:55,280 --> 00:29:57,920
I honestly don't think 70 billion won

492
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:00,880
will be enough to compensate
for the 20 years I lost.

493
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:02,960
But we should handle this realistically.

494
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:07,200
If it wasn't for that darn experiment...

495
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:08,320
Mi-ran!

496
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:11,160
Please lower your voice.

497
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:14,600
I would've had a family by now

498
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:17,840
and lived a happy life. Do you understand?

499
00:30:24,200 --> 00:30:25,760
Listen, Mi-ran.

500
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:29,160
We'll do our best
to come up with a measure.

501
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:31,680
So please give us a little bit more time.

502
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:35,680
We'll think about various ways

503
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:38,240
to soothe your resentment.

504
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:40,680
And of course, it's not like
70 billion won

505
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:44,320
will bring you back
the 20 years that you lost.

506
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:49,720
But try thinking about it
in a different perspective.

507
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:53,600
To be honest, you're
20 years younger than your peers.

508
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:56,080
-Yes, exactly.
-Don't you agree?

509
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:58,360
You survived.

510
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:02,040
It's a better world
compared to 20 years ago.

511
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:04,520
You can totally enjoy your life.

512
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:07,080
What do you think?

513
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:10,840
How about you give it a shot
and get frozen for 20 years?

514
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:14,880
You don't even know what it's like.

515
00:31:21,960 --> 00:31:23,280
Drink a cold cup of water.

516
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:37,120
What are we going to do?

517
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:39,320
She's a complete lunatic!

518
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:41,160
Why did you make her
participate in the experiment?

519
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:44,920
What kind of sane person would
participate in that experiment?

520
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:47,160
We're in big trouble.

521
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:49,080
How are we going to deal with this?

522
00:31:49,160 --> 00:31:51,600
I thought I'd be able to settle everything

523
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:53,680
by giving her my pension.

524
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:55,960
How about we just reveal everything

525
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:57,480
and willingly

526
00:31:57,560 --> 00:31:59,760
get judged by the law?

527
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:02,240
What in the world is wrong with your head?

528
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:03,960
What kind of a dumb idea is that?

529
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:06,520
They're coming out.

530
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:12,920
Let's go, Mi-ran. I'll drive you home.

531
00:32:13,160 --> 00:32:14,920
It's okay, I can walk.

532
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:17,960
Just get in. I'm sure
you're not fully well yet.

533
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:22,160
Of course not. I'm aching all over.

534
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,360
(Seoul, G2590)

535
00:32:40,480 --> 00:32:42,800
I can't believe that car's
still running. Isn't it cool?

536
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:43,920
You're right.

537
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:52,240
If I wasn't frozen for 20 years,

538
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:54,760
Leslie Cheung would still be alive.

539
00:32:56,120 --> 00:32:58,760
How does that make any sense?
Are you a sophist?

540
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:00,720
I told you that he was scheduled
to visit Korea

541
00:33:00,800 --> 00:33:02,640
a few days after the experiment, right?

542
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:05,880
Yes. I even promised
I'd let you see him in person.

543
00:33:05,960 --> 00:33:06,960
Yes.

544
00:33:07,880 --> 00:33:09,400
If I had met him then,

545
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:12,840
I would've helped him
find the desire to live.

546
00:33:14,160 --> 00:33:16,880
He would have had the will to live
while thinking of me.

547
00:33:16,960 --> 00:33:20,600
Then he wouldn't have
ended his life in vain.

548
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:23,520
What is this? I'm speechless.

549
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:26,560
If that's your way of thinking,
then we can assume

550
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:28,640
you might have died in a car accident

551
00:33:28,720 --> 00:33:29,640
if you weren't frozen.

552
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:32,480
Are you serious?
Do you even hear yourself?

553
00:33:32,560 --> 00:33:34,960
It's true, if we follow your logic.

554
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:38,440
You never know what could've
happened to you in 20 years.

555
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:42,040
Life isn't always filled with good things.

556
00:33:42,680 --> 00:33:43,960
Are you going to keep on nitpicking?

557
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:47,840
In those 20 years,
I could've won the lottery too.

558
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:50,720
No, no. That would never happen.

559
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:51,720
Why not?

560
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:53,040
Why is it possible for me to die
in an accident,

561
00:33:53,120 --> 00:33:54,200
but not win the lottery?

562
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:56,640
I'm saying we should consider probability.

563
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:01,880
I could've married Leslie,

564
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:05,480
or a really cool man...

565
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:07,880
Gosh.

566
00:34:08,239 --> 00:34:12,080
Isn't it more likely to meet
a strange guy than a cool guy

567
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:15,080
based on the data you have
from the years you've lived?

568
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:18,639
On what grounds
are you making these comments?

569
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:20,800
Don't tell me

570
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:24,600
you're using my ridiculous
ex-boyfriend for the data?

571
00:34:25,159 --> 00:34:26,199
See?

572
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:29,600
You admitted that your ex-boyfriend
was ridiculous.

573
00:34:29,679 --> 00:34:30,679
No, I...

574
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:33,280
There aren't many cool guys out there,

575
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:38,199
nor do you have high chances
of meeting them

576
00:34:45,679 --> 00:34:46,679
What happened?

577
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:51,840
Did the car die on me because
the air conditioning is too high?

578
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:55,120
Mi-ran.

579
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:57,600
Get out.

580
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:01,440
Get out and take a taxi.

581
00:35:08,040 --> 00:35:10,720
Why... Why isn't this working?

582
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:28,000
Ko...

583
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:30,920
Mi-ran?

584
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:43,840
Is that you, Mi-ran?

585
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:45,880
Hello, Mr. Hwang.

586
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:47,400
It's unbelievable.

587
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:49,960
I heard a lot about you from my mom.

588
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:51,600
-Your mom?
-Yes.

589
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:54,480
Ko Mi-ran is my mother.

590
00:35:58,960 --> 00:35:59,960
Then...

591
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:02,800
what about your mother?

592
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:06,600
She passed away in a car accident
when I was 11.

593
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:09,720
She died at the scene.

594
00:36:10,880 --> 00:36:15,160
Until her death, she missed only one man.

595
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:17,560
Do you know what her last words were?

596
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:23,520
"The only love I had in my life
was Hwang Byung-sim."

597
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:29,560
No, Mi-ran!

598
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:36,840
By the way,

599
00:36:38,080 --> 00:36:40,040
if she died instantly in the car accident,

600
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:42,560
when did she leave her last words?

601
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:55,080
Hey! Did you forget
the herbal medicine on the stove?

602
00:36:55,160 --> 00:36:57,280
It's all burnt! Gosh.

603
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,240
I don't know what to do. Hey!

604
00:37:01,200 --> 00:37:02,440
That jerk!

605
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:15,360
I'm so sick of junk emails.

606
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:16,880
Who is it?

607
00:37:18,640 --> 00:37:19,720
"Mi-ran"?

608
00:37:20,520 --> 00:37:21,720
Who's "Mi-ran"?

609
00:37:24,960 --> 00:37:27,160
Mi-ran?

610
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:31,040
(Kyung-ja, this is Mi-ran.)

611
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:32,400
(Kyung-ja, this is Mi-ran.)

612
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:34,160
Ko Mi-ran?

613
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:36,200
(I'm sorry I'm only replying now.)

614
00:37:36,680 --> 00:37:38,120
(I miss you so much.)

615
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:40,160
Oh, my goodness, Mi-ran.

616
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:42,800
Yes, Kyung-ja.

617
00:37:43,080 --> 00:37:44,560
Mi-ran contacted me.

618
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,480
Mi-ran? Ko Mi-ran?

619
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:47,560
Yes.

620
00:37:48,280 --> 00:37:50,200
She wants to meet.

621
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:53,400
What? Where is she right now?

622
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:56,320
Hey, Nam-tae.

623
00:37:57,080 --> 00:37:58,080
Mi-ran.

624
00:38:00,520 --> 00:38:01,520
Here.

625
00:38:03,520 --> 00:38:05,360
(Mi-ran, Nam-tae)

626
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:07,520
Did you bake this yourself?

627
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:15,080
It's delicious.

628
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:18,360
Mi-ran, I also have

629
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:21,120
this.

630
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:24,520
If you keep rubbing it,

631
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:27,840
it warms up. It's a hand warmer.

632
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:30,320
You were

633
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:34,080
-in the cold all this time.
-Thank you.

634
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:38,440
I'll hold this tight in my hands.

635
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:41,800
Goodnight, Mi-ran.

636
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:56,000
(Park Kyung-ja)

637
00:38:57,840 --> 00:38:59,640
(Let's meet right now.)

638
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:02,080
Kyung-ja.

639
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:08,680
Sitting here like this

640
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:13,520
makes me feel like we went back
to 20 years ago.

641
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:17,960
You're right.

642
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:24,600
Ha-young.

643
00:39:25,680 --> 00:39:26,760
Do you remember?

644
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:28,960
You said

645
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:32,640
you're scared

646
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:36,720
I might turn cold like ice
after the experiment.

647
00:39:40,200 --> 00:39:41,760
I'm not the one who changed,

648
00:39:45,840 --> 00:39:46,920
it's you.

649
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:53,880
I can understand.

650
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:58,800
I'm sure the 20 years I spent
is different from yours.

651
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:03,400
I didn't physically spend
the 20 years like you did,

652
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:06,520
so I was unable to change.
But it must be different for you.

653
00:40:13,920 --> 00:40:16,880
Do I still

654
00:40:19,520 --> 00:40:20,600
look like

655
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:23,360
a woman to you?

656
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:30,480
Yes,

657
00:40:31,640 --> 00:40:32,680
you do.

658
00:40:54,440 --> 00:40:56,400
Where is she? Gosh.

659
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:02,480
Young-sun, look. Isn't that Mi-ran?

660
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:05,880
-Gosh, it's Mi-ran.
-It's her.

661
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:07,760
-Mi-ran!
-Mi-ran!

662
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:11,240
-Gosh, Mi-ran! Mi-ran!
-Mi-ran! Mi-ran!

663
00:41:24,720 --> 00:41:25,920
It's me, it's me.

664
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:27,360
-Kyung-ja.
-Kyung-ja.

665
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:30,160
-Young-sun?
-Young-sun.

666
00:41:30,600 --> 00:41:32,160
Kyung-ja. Young-sun.

667
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:35,720
How... How can this be?

668
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:38,720
I know, right? She didn't change a bit!

669
00:41:39,280 --> 00:41:40,280
Guys.

670
00:41:42,520 --> 00:41:45,240
-Gosh.
-How can this happen?

671
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:51,280
Why haven't you contacted us in 20 years?

672
00:41:51,640 --> 00:41:53,840
I was busy in the US.

673
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:57,160
You're so mean. That's no excuse.

674
00:41:57,760 --> 00:41:59,200
By the way, did you get married?

675
00:41:59,760 --> 00:42:02,000
Not yet. What about you guys?

676
00:42:02,440 --> 00:42:04,360
I know Kyung-ja's dream
was to become a good wife.

677
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:07,360
I guess it was.

678
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:09,520
I'm divorced.

679
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:11,520
I hate all men now.

680
00:42:12,080 --> 00:42:15,160
You won't believe
who this girl is married to.

681
00:42:15,240 --> 00:42:17,520
You don't want to know.

682
00:42:17,600 --> 00:42:19,240
I can't believe it myself.

683
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:27,920
So why did you suddenly disappear
and stop talking to us?

684
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:31,760
We had all kinds of thoughts about
what might have happened to you.

685
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:35,280
She's right. Horrible incidents
were happening around that time.

686
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:37,320
And your mother told us

687
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:39,520
that you went to the US to study.

688
00:42:43,200 --> 00:42:48,000
How can you look exactly the same
as you did 20 years ago?

689
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:50,200
You guys look the same too.

690
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:52,720
I've been taking good care of myself.

691
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:54,960
People do tell me
that I look like I'm in my 20s

692
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,000
all the time.

693
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:58,120
-Cut it out. The thing is,
-I'm tired of it.

694
00:42:58,200 --> 00:43:00,480
you're on a whole other level.

695
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:03,520
-You haven't aged at all.
-Right.

696
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:06,120
-You think so?
-Yes.

697
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:09,720
Maybe it's because I've been
sleeping for the past 20 years.

698
00:43:09,800 --> 00:43:10,960
What are you talking about?

699
00:43:11,040 --> 00:43:13,400
You'd still age though.

700
00:43:14,240 --> 00:43:15,600
So what did you do?

701
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:18,960
Did you undergo
some secret procedures or something?

702
00:43:19,320 --> 00:43:22,040
Yes, tell us the truth.

703
00:43:22,120 --> 00:43:23,280
What did you do?

704
00:43:23,560 --> 00:43:25,840
In the US, they use root cells

705
00:43:25,920 --> 00:43:27,640
It's stem cells, you fool.

706
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:29,120
-It doesn't matter.
-I can't believe you.

707
00:43:29,200 --> 00:43:31,520
I heard they're developing
scientific techniques

708
00:43:31,600 --> 00:43:34,120
that use cells to prevent aging.

709
00:43:34,200 --> 00:43:35,840
-Is that what you did?
-Is that true?

710
00:43:35,920 --> 00:43:37,000
Is that it?

711
00:43:38,680 --> 00:43:39,720
What is it?

712
00:43:43,160 --> 00:43:47,280
I'm grateful that
you guys have been doing so well.

713
00:43:48,520 --> 00:43:50,840
I have to use the bathroom.

714
00:43:57,880 --> 00:44:01,040
Did she live on preservatives
in the US for 20 years?

715
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:04,160
I'm sure she did something in the US.

716
00:44:04,240 --> 00:44:06,200
It can't be Botox or plastic surgery.

717
00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:07,440
It's impossible.

718
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:09,560
When it comes to plastic surgery,
Korea is the best.

719
00:44:09,640 --> 00:44:10,720
I know that.

720
00:44:11,160 --> 00:44:13,400
She's hiding something from us.

721
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:15,040
Medicine has come a long way,

722
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:17,960
but you can't achieve that
with medical procedures only.

723
00:44:18,040 --> 00:44:18,960
Exactly.

724
00:44:19,040 --> 00:44:20,960
Unless she's become a vampire
or been frozen

725
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:24,160
Has she been frozen?

726
00:44:24,240 --> 00:44:25,480
No way.

727
00:44:26,200 --> 00:44:27,440
Impossible.

728
00:44:27,520 --> 00:44:28,840
-No?
-No.

729
00:44:48,600 --> 00:44:49,720
Hi, Mom.

730
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:51,640
My class is over.

731
00:44:53,560 --> 00:44:55,760
By the way,
Dad must be having a hard time.

732
00:44:56,200 --> 00:44:57,800
He's playing the piano alone.

733
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:00,600
He's crying too.

734
00:45:01,200 --> 00:45:02,760
(I'm sure it's hard for him.)

735
00:45:03,160 --> 00:45:06,600
His brother came back after 20 years.

736
00:45:08,240 --> 00:45:10,920
Is the galbi for Table Three ready yet?

737
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:12,600
It's coming!

738
00:45:14,080 --> 00:45:17,160
Go straight home, okay?

739
00:45:17,240 --> 00:45:19,560
(Korean Style Restaurant Jinsagalbi)

740
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:24,360
I'll cut it up later.

741
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:26,760
Are you full?

742
00:45:26,840 --> 00:45:29,440
We ate as much as we wanted.

743
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:31,800
It was so tasty.
We'll definitely come back.

744
00:45:32,240 --> 00:45:34,280
Come again, sir.

745
00:45:36,240 --> 00:45:39,320
Does she think she can make them
come back, looking like that?

746
00:45:39,640 --> 00:45:44,400
Is she putting on lipstick or eating it?

747
00:46:01,920 --> 00:46:02,960
Dad!

748
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:06,480
Are you okay?

749
00:46:06,880 --> 00:46:09,080
After playing the piano
with all the energy I have,

750
00:46:09,480 --> 00:46:11,880
I often fall down like this.

751
00:46:12,640 --> 00:46:14,160
I have low blood pressure.

752
00:46:15,840 --> 00:46:18,800
Then quit playing the piano.

753
00:46:19,160 --> 00:46:20,560
But I'm an artist.

754
00:46:20,640 --> 00:46:22,160
Surviving is more important.

755
00:46:22,240 --> 00:46:23,760
Art comes after that.

756
00:46:25,880 --> 00:46:27,520
Get up.

757
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:32,240
Turn around.

758
00:46:34,320 --> 00:46:36,160
You're the director. Act like one.

759
00:46:36,280 --> 00:46:38,600
Keep your dignity.

760
00:46:38,720 --> 00:46:40,440
I'll go out first.

761
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:43,320
Calm yourself down
and come out in five minutes.

762
00:46:46,480 --> 00:46:48,320
Gosh, I'm dizzy.

763
00:46:51,000 --> 00:46:52,760
Sir! We have a problem.

764
00:46:52,840 --> 00:46:55,240
What is it now?

765
00:46:55,400 --> 00:46:58,040
An article...

766
00:46:58,120 --> 00:46:59,360
("Director Appears after 20 Years")

767
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:02,080
"A TV director
who disappeared 20 years ago "

768
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:05,120
"showed up looking exactly the same,"

769
00:47:05,200 --> 00:47:07,080
"leaving everyone in shock."

770
00:47:12,640 --> 00:47:14,040
("Director Appears after 20 Years")

771
00:47:14,440 --> 00:47:16,880
"Where was he for the past 20 years?"

772
00:47:17,040 --> 00:47:19,400
"What is the broadcasting station hiding?"

773
00:47:19,760 --> 00:47:22,640
"He has no twin brother.
Could it be his doppelganger?"

774
00:47:22,720 --> 00:47:26,000
"Could he have been locked up by aliens?"

775
00:47:26,160 --> 00:47:28,760
"Could he have been
experimented on by them?"

776
00:47:30,800 --> 00:47:32,920
How imaginative.

777
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:36,080
This journalist specializes in mysteries.

778
00:47:36,960 --> 00:47:38,280
Will it be all right?

779
00:47:40,160 --> 00:47:42,480
If people find out
that I came back after 20 years,

780
00:47:42,560 --> 00:47:44,360
it might put someone in danger.

781
00:47:44,600 --> 00:47:46,000
What do you mean?

782
00:47:47,560 --> 00:47:49,800
What happened?

783
00:47:55,920 --> 00:47:57,240
What did I tell you?

784
00:47:57,320 --> 00:48:00,200
Did you see the article about
the director who came back?

785
00:48:00,480 --> 00:48:03,440
I'm sure it has something
to do with Mi-ran.

786
00:48:03,520 --> 00:48:06,400
My hunches are always right.

787
00:48:06,480 --> 00:48:09,800
I had a hunch when my ex-husband
cheated on me too.

788
00:48:12,880 --> 00:48:14,360
I'm having a hunch this time too.

789
00:48:16,440 --> 00:48:17,840
Yes!

790
00:48:18,160 --> 00:48:20,760
You don't trust my hunch?
I'm 100 percent sure.

791
00:48:21,120 --> 00:48:24,760
Anyway, what's important is
that she came back safe.

792
00:48:25,160 --> 00:48:26,560
("Invitation to the Unconscious")

793
00:48:33,600 --> 00:48:37,520
Why did Ko Mi-ran show up
in my unconscious mind?

794
00:48:39,400 --> 00:48:41,240
What could be the reason?

795
00:48:42,200 --> 00:48:44,480
Is she an existential being?

796
00:48:45,040 --> 00:48:46,160
Or...

797
00:48:48,400 --> 00:48:50,000
("Director Appears after 20 Years")

798
00:48:51,240 --> 00:48:53,560
Oh, my. What will happen to my son?

799
00:48:54,000 --> 00:48:55,680
The broadcasting station people

800
00:48:55,760 --> 00:48:57,840
need to plan something.

801
00:48:57,960 --> 00:48:59,720
Those jerks!

802
00:49:02,320 --> 00:49:04,400
He doesn't look like my brother.

803
00:49:04,920 --> 00:49:07,080
Look at his facial expression and eyes.

804
00:49:07,360 --> 00:49:08,840
He's someone else.

805
00:49:13,600 --> 00:49:15,520
What should we do now?

806
00:49:15,960 --> 00:49:18,120
People won't leave us alone.

807
00:49:20,400 --> 00:49:24,680
The picture doesn't do him justice.

808
00:49:25,080 --> 00:49:26,480
He looks better in real life.

809
00:49:27,240 --> 00:49:28,800
I'll go to the broadcasting station

810
00:49:28,880 --> 00:49:30,680
and settle things with them.

811
00:49:30,760 --> 00:49:32,600
I'll teach those jerks a lesson!

812
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:34,240
-Okay, let's go.
-Mom, I'll come with you.

813
00:49:34,320 --> 00:49:36,240
Stop! Grandma.

814
00:49:36,480 --> 00:49:38,000
We need to calm down.

815
00:49:38,080 --> 00:49:41,480
Uncle becoming a celebrity
wouldn't hurt us.

816
00:49:47,440 --> 00:49:49,200
Now that Professor Hwang has woken up,

817
00:49:49,280 --> 00:49:50,720
we're over the hump.

818
00:49:52,800 --> 00:49:54,600
Is each cryonic capsule

819
00:49:54,880 --> 00:49:56,640
sponsored by someone?

820
00:49:57,160 --> 00:49:59,040
Going into a cryonic capsule

821
00:49:59,120 --> 00:50:01,000
costs a fortune.

822
00:50:04,280 --> 00:50:07,120
How were our capsules financed then?

823
00:50:07,360 --> 00:50:10,320
They were sponsored
by Johnson McCarthy Foundation.

824
00:50:11,720 --> 00:50:13,760
Professor Hwang wished to achieve this

825
00:50:13,840 --> 00:50:15,480
using Korean capital and technology only.

826
00:50:15,560 --> 00:50:18,440
But I guess that's failed.

827
00:50:18,760 --> 00:50:20,680
It's been sponsored by McCarthy Foundation

828
00:50:20,760 --> 00:50:22,560
for 20 years already.

829
00:50:22,640 --> 00:50:23,680
You're right.

830
00:50:24,200 --> 00:50:25,480
By the way,

831
00:50:26,880 --> 00:50:28,760
I have a question.

832
00:50:29,040 --> 00:50:30,240
Go ahead.

833
00:50:31,440 --> 00:50:33,040
It's about my body temperature.

834
00:50:35,240 --> 00:50:37,240
Is my normal body temperature

835
00:50:37,760 --> 00:50:39,600
31.5C after the experiment?

836
00:50:39,760 --> 00:50:40,960
That's correct.

837
00:50:42,120 --> 00:50:45,160
The critical point is 33C.

838
00:50:50,360 --> 00:50:52,080
(The Disappearance
of Director Ma Dong-chan)

839
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:56,840
He was declared dead,

840
00:50:56,920 --> 00:50:58,760
but there were many suspicious things.

841
00:51:00,920 --> 00:51:03,520
This man is the murder suspect
of Professor Johnson.

842
00:51:03,920 --> 00:51:06,920
If he was 35 years old back then,
he'd be 55 years old by now.

843
00:51:07,000 --> 00:51:09,520
Professor Hwang witnessed
Professor Johnson get murdered.

844
00:51:09,600 --> 00:51:11,200
And he got into an accident

845
00:51:11,280 --> 00:51:13,760
on his way to meet a CIA agent
to make a statement.

846
00:51:14,040 --> 00:51:15,240
So in other words,

847
00:51:15,760 --> 00:51:18,320
it's highly possible that this man
was the one who caused

848
00:51:18,400 --> 00:51:20,200
Professor Hwang's car to explode.

849
00:51:20,320 --> 00:51:22,400
Why did the CIA suddenly put an end
to the investigation

850
00:51:22,480 --> 00:51:23,840
when even the Korean police
are suspicious about him?

851
00:51:23,920 --> 00:51:26,160
He became a Russian senator.

852
00:51:26,560 --> 00:51:28,200
He's not someone they can mess with.

853
00:51:30,640 --> 00:51:32,480
So you think he's the culprit?

854
00:51:33,960 --> 00:51:35,120
But what if it's not him?

855
00:51:36,040 --> 00:51:36,960
(Unsung Group CEO, Lee Seok-du)

856
00:51:37,040 --> 00:51:38,960
I think we should carry out
a background check.

857
00:51:39,200 --> 00:51:42,720
Are you saying Professor Hwang
might not be dead?

858
00:51:42,800 --> 00:51:45,200
That's right. No one succeeded
in finding his dead body.

859
00:51:45,560 --> 00:51:47,400
And there's something very important.

860
00:51:47,960 --> 00:51:51,520
A director that disappeared
20 years ago suddenly showed up.

861
00:51:52,360 --> 00:51:55,000
But the thing is, he looks exactly
the same as he did 20 years ago.

862
00:51:56,960 --> 00:51:58,240
And I even heard
that he was gathering information

863
00:51:58,320 --> 00:51:59,560
about Professor Hwang's
experiment back then.

864
00:51:59,640 --> 00:52:01,520
Are you sure about that?

865
00:52:01,760 --> 00:52:04,120
Yes, I'm sure. I even
read an article about it today.

866
00:52:13,920 --> 00:52:14,920
What should I do, sir?

867
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:18,160
I want you to check
if Professor Hwang is alive or not.

868
00:52:18,240 --> 00:52:19,240
And

869
00:52:20,200 --> 00:52:24,400
do a background check about that director.

870
00:52:25,080 --> 00:52:26,040
Okay, sir.

871
00:52:26,120 --> 00:52:30,400
And if it turns out
that Professor Hwang is still alive,

872
00:52:31,960 --> 00:52:33,160
we should get rid of him.

873
00:52:36,320 --> 00:52:37,400
By the way,

874
00:52:38,560 --> 00:52:41,080
do people still think the Russian senator

875
00:52:42,760 --> 00:52:46,720
is the one who killed Professor Hwang?

876
00:52:47,320 --> 00:52:48,480
Yes, I think so.

877
00:52:49,160 --> 00:52:51,160
(Unsung Group CEO, Lee Seok-du)

878
00:53:08,920 --> 00:53:10,080
(A cryonics experiment?)

879
00:53:11,080 --> 00:53:12,160
My goodness.

880
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:14,400
I was so shocked the moment I saw you

881
00:53:14,480 --> 00:53:17,040
because you hadn't changed at all.
So that's what happened?

882
00:53:17,480 --> 00:53:20,600
You participated
in that experiment yourself?

883
00:53:21,640 --> 00:53:25,000
I guess that's why you met
Professor Hwang back then.

884
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:26,720
There's also one more thing
you need to know.

885
00:53:27,720 --> 00:53:29,560
-Professor Hwang isn't dead.
-What?

886
00:53:29,760 --> 00:53:32,800
He's still alive,
but no one's supposed to know.

887
00:53:32,920 --> 00:53:34,880
I'm telling you because I need your help.

888
00:53:35,040 --> 00:53:37,360
I was also suspicious
about his death back then.

889
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:41,120
By the way, are you feeling okay?

890
00:53:45,640 --> 00:53:47,080
Can I borrow your cell phone?

891
00:53:47,640 --> 00:53:50,200
(The number you've dialed
is not available now.)

892
00:53:55,560 --> 00:53:59,480
My gosh, how long is he
planning to live like a caveman?

893
00:53:59,760 --> 00:54:02,000
He really should get a new cell phone.

894
00:54:07,040 --> 00:54:08,080
Who's calling?

895
00:54:10,800 --> 00:54:11,840
Hello?

896
00:54:12,560 --> 00:54:13,560
(Hey, it's me.)

897
00:54:14,920 --> 00:54:16,920
-Did you get a new cell phone?
-No, not yet.

898
00:54:18,560 --> 00:54:20,840
Did you get home safely that day?

899
00:54:21,120 --> 00:54:23,120
You totally abandoned me
in the middle of the road.

900
00:54:23,520 --> 00:54:24,960
I guess that made you feel uneasy.

901
00:54:27,400 --> 00:54:30,000
Do you feel sick by any chance?

902
00:54:30,360 --> 00:54:33,120
I'm aching all over.
How do you expect me to be fine?

903
00:54:35,640 --> 00:54:36,680
I'm sorry.

904
00:54:40,280 --> 00:54:41,720
Make sure you don't get a fever.

905
00:54:42,400 --> 00:54:43,600
Apparently, we need to be careful.

906
00:54:44,840 --> 00:54:46,000
What's that supposed to mean?

907
00:54:46,760 --> 00:54:48,880
Anyway, if you ever get a fever

908
00:54:48,960 --> 00:54:50,880
or feel sick in any kind of way,
call me right away.

909
00:54:54,680 --> 00:54:56,720
Let's talk again, face to face.
I'll hang up for now.

910
00:55:02,840 --> 00:55:06,160
What's his deal? I really don't know
what I should do with him.

911
00:55:09,600 --> 00:55:11,680
He told me to call, but he doesn't
even have a cell phone.

912
00:55:21,160 --> 00:55:23,280
-Who was that?
-Another subject of the experiment.

913
00:55:24,360 --> 00:55:25,800
There's another person?

914
00:55:25,880 --> 00:55:28,280
Shouldn't you know that
if you went through my texts?

915
00:55:28,360 --> 00:55:29,320
Didn't you get the hint?

916
00:55:29,400 --> 00:55:32,120
I thought it was about another experiment.

917
00:55:32,200 --> 00:55:33,920
You guys participated
in that experiment together?

918
00:55:34,280 --> 00:55:35,880
You were both frozen?

919
00:55:45,920 --> 00:55:47,120
(Job Fair, Hanguk University)

920
00:55:56,280 --> 00:55:58,520
Watch out for the ball! Watch out!

921
00:56:08,440 --> 00:56:10,520
Are you here for an interview?
Did you bring your resume?

922
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:11,560
Yes.

923
00:56:11,640 --> 00:56:13,360
(Resume)

924
00:56:13,440 --> 00:56:15,160
"Ko Mi-ran".

925
00:56:16,680 --> 00:56:17,680
How old are you?

926
00:56:19,680 --> 00:56:20,600
(Date of Birth: February 14, 1976)

927
00:56:20,680 --> 00:56:22,760
You were born in 1976?

928
00:56:24,080 --> 00:56:25,680
Did you enter university at a late age?

929
00:56:25,760 --> 00:56:27,320
No, not exactly.

930
00:56:28,280 --> 00:56:30,960
It's because of something personal.

931
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:35,280
Let's see your work experiences.
All you did was participate

932
00:56:35,360 --> 00:56:38,480
as a subject in "Infinite
Experiment Paradise" in 1999.

933
00:56:39,080 --> 00:56:40,080
Yes.

934
00:56:43,080 --> 00:56:47,000
You're 44 years old, and you want
to get a job as a new recruit?

935
00:56:52,880 --> 00:56:55,800
You're not married,
and you don't even have a job.

936
00:56:56,160 --> 00:56:57,720
What in the world did you do?

937
00:56:59,920 --> 00:57:02,160
I was frozen in the freezer, okay?

938
00:57:06,560 --> 00:57:07,760
Isn't she really cute?

939
00:57:08,480 --> 00:57:09,520
Yes, she is.

940
00:57:11,840 --> 00:57:14,760
My gosh, does that mean
the rumors were true?

941
00:57:15,320 --> 00:57:18,560
Shouldn't our broadcasting station
do an exclusive cover on this?

942
00:57:18,880 --> 00:57:20,240
This is a huge scoop.

943
00:57:20,320 --> 00:57:23,040
Get back to work! A huge scoop, my foot!

944
00:57:28,720 --> 00:57:29,680
We need to talk.

945
00:57:29,760 --> 00:57:31,840
Sure, go ahead.

946
00:57:32,080 --> 00:57:34,080
Why didn't you look for me

947
00:57:35,160 --> 00:57:36,280
when I disappeared?

948
00:57:37,360 --> 00:57:38,360
What?

949
00:57:39,080 --> 00:57:40,200
Well...

950
00:57:40,280 --> 00:57:43,200
And why didn't you tell the cops
about the experiment?

951
00:57:44,160 --> 00:57:46,720
If you had told them what happened,
they could've done an investigation.

952
00:57:47,240 --> 00:57:48,160
Well...

953
00:57:48,240 --> 00:57:51,200
-Wait...
-How could you do this to me?

954
00:57:51,280 --> 00:57:53,280
Dong-chan, please...

955
00:57:54,480 --> 00:57:56,680
Dong-chan, the CC...

956
00:57:56,760 --> 00:57:58,560
What? What are you trying to say?

957
00:57:58,640 --> 00:58:00,080
The CCTV.

958
00:58:00,680 --> 00:58:02,720
You can't hit me.

959
00:58:02,800 --> 00:58:05,280
The world has changed
compared to 20 years ago.

960
00:58:05,360 --> 00:58:07,440
You could end up losing your job.

961
00:58:07,520 --> 00:58:09,720
Hey, are you trying to lecture me?

962
00:58:09,800 --> 00:58:12,800
Dong-chan, I'm really sorry.

963
00:58:13,280 --> 00:58:16,360
But I really had no choice.

964
00:58:16,440 --> 00:58:17,520
Darn it!

965
00:58:26,320 --> 00:58:28,840
Did you get rid of all the video footage?

966
00:58:31,000 --> 00:58:32,400
What about Jin, the floor director?

967
00:58:33,560 --> 00:58:35,560
Tell me everything you know that I don't.

968
00:58:36,280 --> 00:58:37,880
After you disappeared,

969
00:58:38,280 --> 00:58:40,480
we put an end to that project.

970
00:58:40,920 --> 00:58:44,280
There was nothing I could do back then.

971
00:58:44,480 --> 00:58:47,440
I was just an assistant director
who had absolutely no power.

972
00:58:48,080 --> 00:58:49,640
I just did what I was told.

973
00:58:49,720 --> 00:58:52,520
And right now, you're just a chief
who still has no power.

974
00:58:52,600 --> 00:58:54,200
You still follow orders, don't you?

975
00:58:54,280 --> 00:58:56,640
Dong-chan, this is tormenting for me too.

976
00:58:56,720 --> 00:58:58,160
We worked together for years.

977
00:58:58,640 --> 00:58:59,680
How could you of all people

978
00:58:59,760 --> 00:59:02,640
pretend like nothing ever happened
even when I disappeared?

979
00:59:05,320 --> 00:59:08,080
You don't even deserve
to be called a human being.

980
00:59:26,560 --> 00:59:27,640
What brings you here?

981
00:59:28,320 --> 00:59:32,160
Director Ma, can you get me a job?

982
00:59:32,480 --> 00:59:33,680
A job?

983
00:59:34,440 --> 00:59:35,680
Yes, I want a job.

984
00:59:36,600 --> 00:59:38,120
Where?

985
00:59:40,320 --> 00:59:41,800
Right here at the broadcasting station.

986
00:59:44,320 --> 00:59:45,320
Here?

987
01:00:23,600 --> 01:00:25,880
(Melting Me Softly)

988
01:00:26,680 --> 01:00:29,720
You're asking me to work
as an intern for three months?

989
01:00:29,920 --> 01:00:32,120
(Something's weird about her.)

990
01:00:32,800 --> 01:00:34,160
Dong-chan! Please don't cause a fuss.

991
01:00:34,240 --> 01:00:36,320
I'm not going to lie!

992
01:00:36,520 --> 01:00:37,720
(You also didn't look for me)

993
01:00:37,880 --> 01:00:40,840
just like the others even when you knew?

994
01:00:41,240 --> 01:00:42,720
(Do we need to keep living like this?)

995
01:00:42,800 --> 01:00:44,240
(This is really cool.)

996
01:00:45,440 --> 01:00:48,480
(Why do you think they locked us up
in a refrigerated container?)

997
01:00:49,040 --> 01:00:50,000
Are you okay?

998
01:00:50,080 --> 01:00:52,120
Mi-ran! Mi-ran, wake up!

999
01:00:53,120 --> 01:00:54,120
(I'm sorry.)
